  "derivation_layer": {
    "source_latex": "% BEGIN TZP DERIVATION LAYER\n\\tzpsection{Derivation Layer}\n\\paragraph{Primary Equation.}\n\\begin{equation}\n\\lim_{x\\to p}R_T(x)=\\infty .\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Primary Derivation.}\nFrom ID 0016, the regularized Trawin curvature is:\n\n\\begin{equation}\nR_T(x)=R(x)+f(x).\n\\end{equation}\n\nA regular TZP curvature condition occurs when:\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\lim_{x\\to p}R_T(x)<\\infty .\n\\end{equation}\n\nA curvature singularity occurs when this limiting value fails to remain finite. Therefore the singular condition is:\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\boxed{\n\\lim_{x\\to p}R_T(x)=\\infty .\n}\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Interpretation.}\nID 0022 defines the failure condition of the regulator: the TZP becomes a true curvature singularity when $R_T$ diverges.\n% END TZP DERIVATION LAYER"
